Sentencas: The interfacial properties of electrolyte materials have a crucial impact on the ionic conductivity of solid batteries and solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: Here we construct cuprospinel CuFe2O4 (CFO)-ZnO composite as a functional electrolyte for fuel cell device.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: In an optimal composition of 0.3CFO-0.7ZnO electrolyte fuel cell, the maximum power output of 675 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical properties and electrochemical performance are strongly dependent on the ratios between CFO and ZnO in CFO-ZnO composite.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: Notably, surprising fuel cell performance with high ionic conductivity is attained by constructing this p-type CFO composited with n-type ZnO. Proton conduction was further verified experimentally.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: The interfacial ionic conduction pathway between the two constituent phases plays a vital role to enhance the proton conductivity, and the bulk p-n heterojunction can block internal electronic pass.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: An excellent current and power densities of CFO-ZnO composite are observed along with a high conductivity of 0.35 S.cm(-1) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells

Sentencas: This work opens a new perspective for the semiconductor materials that can widely be developed for electrolytes, based on their tunable band structure.
Titulo: Developing cuprospinel CuFe2O4-ZnO semiconductor heterostructure as a proton conducting electrolyte for advanced fuel cells
